The person responsible fired off the message without realising they'd copied in 840,000 co-workers. LONDON An email that was accidentally sent to all 840,000 National Health Service staff in England has caused chaos for health workers in the United Kingdom. The message clogged up the system and important, confidential and sometimes urgent emails between staff about patients couldn t get through. The National Health Service email system was left in disarray for hours. Reports that the message was accidentally sent out by one of the IT staff have been denied but the culprit s identity has not been revealed.The person responsible fired off the message without realising they had copied in 840,000 of their co-workers. The distribution list was quickly cancelled but not before the situation had been exacerbated when users hit 'reply all' to complain.(Edited by Leeto M Khoza)